The paper discusses the use of a Dynamic Distributed Dimensional Data Model (D4M) library for representing and analyzing streaming network data, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the optimization of memory hierarchy for streaming updates, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance achieved on the MIT SuperCloud, which is a topic related to system performance (cs.SI).
